otor vehicle that the employee is authorized to drive.  Drivers must agree to operate University motor vehicles in accordance with applicable State and Local laws, and University regulations.  Drivers must have a copy of their Departmental Driver Approval Form  on file with their department. (This document may not open properly in all browsers.  If you get an error message, please download the file and open it in Acrobat Reader or try a different browser.)      Reserving a Vehicle   Call the CARS Reservation Office at (312) 99 6-2886 (6-AUTO) to reserve a vehicle. Please have the following information available:    Department Name  Drivers Name & Telephone  Date and Time of Vehicle Pick-up  Date and Time of Return  Destination  Vehicle Type (sedan, 7-passenger, 9-Passenger, 15 Passenger)  C-FOP account number      Vehicle Pick-Up   You may pick-up your vehicle on the day of your reservation during CARS business hours:    Monday through Friday from 7:00AM to 4:30PM   If you need to leave before 7:00AM, please come in the day prior to complete your reservation. If you are leaving on Saturday or Sunday, please come in on the Friday prior. You MUST bring the following items with you:   A completed and SIGNED (by department head)  Car Release Order form  . (This document may not open properly in all browsers.  If you get an error message, please download the file and open it in Acrobat Reader or try a different browser.)  Your current drivers license  Alternate drivers (any authorized driver in addition to the primary driver whose name is listed on the Car Release Order Form) must read, provide the information requested on page three (3), and sign the Alternate Drivers Car Release Certification Form  . (This document may not open properly in all browsers.  If you get an error message, please download the file and open it in Acrobat Reader or try a different browser.)  All drivers and alternate must present their current driver’s license for inspection. NO EXCEPTIONS!      Vehicle Return/Cancellation Policy   Upon return, fill out the mileage card and bring the card and vehicle keys into the office. After office hours, you may use key drop box in the rear of the Transportation facility.  Late Returns  If you are unable to return on your specified day, please inform the CARS office as soon as possible at (312) 99 6-2886 . You may be charged for additional days.  Cancellation policy  If you have reserved a vehicle, you must cancel the reservation no later than 24-hours prior to your scheduled pick-up date. Otherwise, a one-day rental will be charged to your account.      Location and Hours   The CARS office is located in the Transportation Facility ( View Map ).  Address : Transportation Facility (MC 269), 1351 South Morgan Street, Chicago, IL 60607  Phone : (312) 99 6-2886 — Fax: (312) 41 3-4093  Office Hours : 7:00 am to 4:30 pm (CT) Monday through Friday      Vehicles    Back to main content           CARS    Chauffeur Service               UIC Logo        Transportation         Policies    Web Privacy Notice      Related Links    Facilities Management    Office of the Vice Chancellor of Administrative Services         Contact   1351 South Morgan Street  Phone: (312) 996-2842  Fax: (312) 996-0165  rides@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings     